  "Range 是 Excel 操作的核心": "Range is the core of Excel work",
  "在 VBA 里几乎所有对单元格的操作都从 Range 对象开始。Range(\"A1\") 表示「这个工作表上的 A1 单元格」。注意它本身是一个对象，不是值——你要再访问它的属性才能拿到里面的内容。最常用的属性就是 .Value，代表单元格当前显示的数据。": "In VBA almost every cell operation starts from a Range object. Range(\"A1\") means \"cell A1 on this worksheet\". Note it is an object, not a value — you must access a property to get the content inside. The most common one is .Value, the data the cell currently holds.",
  "先定位工作表，再取 A1 的 .Value": "Locate the worksheet, then read .Value of A1",
  "养成习惯：永远先 Set ws，再用 ws.Range，别裸写 Range——那样会落到「当前激活的表」上，很容易读错表。": "Make it a habit: always Set ws first, then use ws.Range. Don't write a bare Range — it falls onto whichever sheet is active and easily reads the wrong one.",
  "为什么用 Variant 接住": "Why catch it with Variant",
  "单元格可以装数字、文本、日期、甚至错误值。如果你声明成 Long 去接一个文本单元格，运行时就会报「类型不匹配」。进阶阶段我们追求稳：用 Variant 接住，先拿到再说，后续需要时再判断类型。": "A cell may hold a number, text, a date, or even an error value. If you declare a Long and read a text cell, you get a runtime \"type mismatch\". At this level we play safe: catch it in a Variant first, then decide the type later if needed.",
  "Variant 能接住任意单元格内容": "Variant can hold any cell content",
